'''Çağlar Söyüncü''' ({{IPA|tr|tʃaːˈɫaɾ sœjynˈdʒy}}; born 23 May 1996) is a Turkish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

Söyüncü's first senior professional team was the Turkish second division [[Altınordu F.K.|Altınordu]]. In the summer of 2016, he joined [[SC Freiburg]] of Germany's [[Bundesliga]], before moving to [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] in 2018. He made 132 total appearances for Leicester, winning the [[FA Cup]] and [[FA Community Shield]] in 2021. In 2023, he moved to [[Atlético Madrid]] of [[La Liga]] and soon on to Fenerbahçe, initially on loan.

Söyüncü made his senior national team debut in 2016 and has earned over 50 caps for Turkey. He was part of the Turkish squad at [[UEFA Euro 2020]].

==Club career==
===Altınordu===
Söyüncü began his senior professional career with [[Altınordu F.K.|Altınordu]] in the [[TFF First League]], the second level of the Turkish football league system. During the 2015–16 season with Altınordu, Söyüncü was linked with [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]],<ref name="2016 Besiktas Interest">{{cite news |date=24 April 2016 |title=Beşiktaş'tan Eto'o bombası! |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/besiktastan-etoo-bombasi-40093776 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20191002115521/http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/besiktastan-etoo-bombasi-40093776 |archive-date=2 October 2019 |access-date=7 November 2019 |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |language=Tr}}</ref> [[Galatasaray S.K.|Galatasaray]] and [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]], but he selected the Bundesliga because he thought it was better choice for his career and his improvement.<ref name="Confession about Çağlar Söyüncü">{{cite news |date=20 May 2016 |title=Çağlar Söyüncü için itiraf:Beşiktaş ve Sevilla |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/caglar-soyuncu-icin-itiraf--besiktas-2248697-skorerhaber/ |access-date=17 March 2017 |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |language=tr}}</ref>

===SC Freiburg===
On 24 May 2016, in the [[List of German football transfers summer 2016|2016 Bundesliga summer transfer window]], Söyüncü joined German side [[SC Freiburg]], which was promoted to the top flight competition of Germany for the [[2016–17 Bundesliga|2016–17 season]].<ref name="SC Freiburg Transfer 1">{{cite web |date=24 May 2016 |title=Offiziell: Söyüncü schlägt im Breisgau auf |url=https://www.kicker.de/offiziell_soeyuencue-schlaegt-im-breisgau-auf-652549/artikel |access-date=6 October 2016 |publisher=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]] |language=de}}</ref><ref name="SC Freiburg Transfer 2">{{cite web |date=24 May 2016 |title=Freiburg sign Turkey defender Caglar Söyüncü |url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblsp-sc-freiburg-sign-turkey-defender-caglar-soyuncu.jsp |access-date=8 October 2016 |publisher=www.bundesliga.com |archive-date=5 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105224402/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblsp-sc-freiburg-sign-turkey-defender-caglar-soyuncu.jsp |url-status=dead }}</ref> He is the first Turkish footballer who made a transfer to the [[Bundesliga]] directly from the [[TFF First League]], the second-highest professional level football league of Turkey.<ref name="Al Jazeera: Bundesliga transfer">{{cite web |date=24 May 2016 |title=1. Lig'den yurt dışına ilk transfer |url=http://www.aljazeera.com.tr/haber/1-ligden-yurt-disina-ilk-transfer |access-date=6 October 2016 |publisher=[[Al Jazeera Türk]] |language=tr}}</ref>

He made his Bundesliga debut away against [[Hertha Berlin]] which ended in a 2–1 loss, on 28 August 2016.<ref name="Bundesliga Debut">{{cite news |date=28 August 2016 |title=Çağlar Söyüncü Freiburg ile ilk maçına çıktı |url=http://www.fanatik.com.tr/2016/08/28/caglar-soyuncu-freiburg-ile-ilk-macina-cikti-1250016 |access-date=8 October 2016 |publisher=[[Fanatik (Turkey)|Fanatik]] |language=tr}}</ref> He was linked with [[Lille OSC|Lille]], [[A.S. Roma|Roma]], and [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]] during the mid-season transfer window of the 2016–17 season.<ref name="Four Four Two Turkish Edition: 2016–17 winter transfer window">{{cite web |date=2 February 2017 |title=Çağlar Söyüncü'nün yıldızı parlıyor |url=http://fourfourtwo.com.tr/2017/02/02/%C3%A7a%C4%9Flar-s%C3%B6y%C3%BCnc%C3%BCn%C3%BCn-y%C4%B1ld%C4%B1z%C4%B1-parl%C4%B1yor/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170610234828/http://fourfourtwo.com.tr/2017/02/02/%c3%a7a%c4%9flar-s%c3%b6y%c3%bcnc%c3%bcn%c3%bcn-y%c4%b1ld%c4%b1z%c4%b1-parl%c4%b1yor/ |archive-date=10 June 2017 |access-date=9 February 2017 |publisher=[[Four Four Two|Four Four Two Turkish Edition]] |language=tr}}</ref> [[Manchester City F.C|Manchester City]] was also reported to be interested in Söyüncü.<ref name="Man City link">{{cite news |date=8 February 2017 |title=Guardiola'nın hedefindeki Türk: Çağlar Söyüncü |url=http://www.fanatik.com.tr/2017/02/07/guardiola-nin-hedefindeki-turk-caglar-soyuncu-1276711 |access-date=9 February 2017 |publisher=[[Fanatik (Turkey)|Fanatik]] |language=tr}}</ref>

===Leicester City===
On 9 August 2018, Söyüncü joined English [[Premier League]] side [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |date=9 August 2018 |title=Leicester City Agree Çağlar Söyüncü Transfer |url=https://www.lcfc.com/news/799283/leicester-city-agree-alar-sync-transfer/press-release |access-date=9 August 2018 |publisher=Leicester City F.C.}}</ref> He signed for an apparent £18 million transfer fee, possibly rising to £20 million with add-ons.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leicester City 'agree Caglar Soyuncu fee'|url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/fb_332793.html |access-date=2020-12-01|website=Sports Mole|date=9 August 2018 |language=en-GB}}</ref> Söyüncü had his Premier League debut on 27 October 2018 at the [[King Power Stadium]] where Leicester shared points with [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] following the final score of 1–1.<ref name="Premier League Debut">{{cite news|title=As it happened: Leicester City 1-1 West Ham United|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/october/27-october/it-happened-leicester-city-1-1-west-ham-united|publisher=[[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]|date=27 October 2018|access-date=7 October 2019|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20191107154808/https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/october/27-october/it-happened-leicester-city-1-1-west-ham-united|archive-date=7 November 2019}}</ref>

Söyüncü scored his first Premier League goal in Leicester's 11th game of the [[2019–20 Premier League|2019–20 season]] on 3 November 2019 against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] at [[Selhurst Park]], a 2–0 win.<ref name="First Premier League Goal (1)">{{cite news|author=Saj Chowdhury |title=Crystal Palace 0-2 Leicester: Caglar Soyuncu and Jamie Vardy scores as Foxes go third|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50197728|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=3 November 2019|access-date=7 November 2019 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20191107153511/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50197728|archive-date=7 November 2019}}</ref><ref name="First Premier League Goal (2)">{{cite news |title=Çağlar Söyüncü gol attı, İngiltere sallandı! |url=https://www.haberturk.com/caglar-soyuncu-gol-atti-ingiltere-sallandi-2537016-spor |archive-url=https://archive.today/20191108131848/https://www.haberturk.com/caglar-soyuncu-gol-atti-ingiltere-sallandi-2537016-spor |archive-date=8 November 2019 |access-date=8 November 2019 |publisher=[[Habertürk]] |language=Tr}}</ref> His performances during the 2019–20 season earned him a place in the Premier League [[PFA Team of the Year]].<ref name=":1920"/>

[[File:Çağlar Söyüncü.jpg|thumb|313x313px|Söyüncü after heading the ball during a Leicester City match in 2021]]
On 11 May 2021, Söyüncü scored the winning goal for Leicester City in a 2–1 away victory over [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], to be their first win at [[Old Trafford]] since 1998.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56990159 |title=Manchester United 1–2 Leicester City |website=BBC Sport |date=11 May 2021}}</ref> Four days later he played in the [[2021 FA Cup final]] against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], a 1–0 win; Jacob Steinburg of ''[[The Guardian]]'' said he stood firm after fellow defender [[Jonny Evans]] was substituted with injury.<ref>{{cite news |title=Chelsea 0-1 Leicester City: FA Cup final player ratings |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/may/15/chelsea-leicester-city-fa-cup-final-player-ratings |access-date=16 July 2024 |work=The Guardian |date=15 May 2021}}</ref> In August, he featured in the [[2021 FA Community Shield]], a 1–0 win against league champions [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hytner |first1=David |title=Iheanacho punishes wasteful City to win Community Shield for Leicester |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/aug/07/leicester-manchester-city-community-shield-match-report |access-date=16 July 2024 |work=The Observer |date=7 August 2021}}</ref>

During the 2022–23 season Söyüncü found himself out of the first 11, despite having played more than 20 matches per season for the previous three seasons. This was allegedly due to a personality clash with manager [[Brendan Rodgers]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Blackwell |first=Jordan |date=15 October 2022 |title=Soyuncu set to be overlooked again as Rodgers explains thinking |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/soyuncu-leicester-rodgers-evans-amartey-7707273 |access-date=20 August 2023 |website=Leicestershire Live}}</ref> Söyüncü impressed when he was restored to the team after [[Dean Smith (footballer, born 1971)|Dean Smith]] took over as manager, however this was insufficient to prevent relegation.<ref>{{cite web |last=Blackwell |first=Jordan |date=15 April 2023 |title='Fire in eyes' of Soyuncu won over Smith to end period as Leicester City outcast |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/how-caglar-soyuncu-won-over-8356087 |access-date=20 August 2023 |website=Leicestershire Live}}</ref> On 5 June 2023, following the club's relegation from the [[Premier League]], it was announced that Söyüncü and six other first team players would be leaving the club upon the expiration of their contracts at the end of the month.<ref>{{cite news |title=Seven Players To Depart LCFC |url=https://www.lcfc.com/news/3529945/seven-players-to-depart-lcfc |access-date=24 June 2023 |work=Leicester City F.C. |date=5 June 2023}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
On 5 July 2023, following Leicester City's relegation from Premier League, Söyüncü joined  Spanish [[La Liga]] side [[Atlético Madrid]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite news |title=Caglar Soyuncu: Turkey defender completes Atletico Madrid move |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66115094 |access-date=16 July 2024 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=5 July 2023}}</ref> He played nine games, of which six in the league (115 minutes), two in the [[UEFA Champions League]] (59 minutes) and one half of a [[Copa del Rey]] match.<ref name=marca>{{cite news |last1=Medina |first1=David G. |title=Soyuncu, un negocio redondo para el Atlético|trans-title=Söyüncü, a proftiable business for Atlético |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/atletico/2024/07/01/66827223268e3ece338b458f.html |access-date=16 July 2024 |work=Marca |date=1 July 2024 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He was sent off in a 1–0 win over [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] on 23 December for a foul on [[Lucas Ocampos]], only four minutes after coming on as a substitute.<ref>{{cite news |title=Llorente earns 10-man Atletico 1-0 win over Sevilla |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/674046 |access-date=16 July 2024 |publisher=ESPN |date=23 December 2023}}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
On 29 January 2024, Söyüncü signed for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] on loan for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news |date=29 January 2024 |title=Ailemize hoş geldin Çağlar Söyüncü |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/1/ailemize-hos-geldin-caglar-soyuncu |access-date=29 January 2024 |work=Fenerbahce.org |language=tr}}</ref> On 3 February 2024, he make his [[Süper Lig]] debut in his career against [[Antalyaspor]] in a 2-0 away win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/2/bitexen-antalyaspor-0-2-fenerbahce |title=Bitexen Antalyaspor 0-2 Fenerbahçe |access-date=27 January 2025 |work=Fenerbahce.org |date=3 February 2024 |language=tr}}</ref> Four days later, on 7 February 2024, he made his [[Turkish Cup]] debut with the team against [[Gaziantep F.K.|Gaziantep]] in a 2-0 away win and helped his team to reached quarter final.<ref>{{cite news |date=7 February 2024 |title=Fenerbahçemiz, Ziraat Türkiye Kupası’nda çeyrek finale yükseldi |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/2/fenerbahcemiz-ziraat-turkiye-kupasi-nda-ceyrek-finale-yukseldi |access-date=27 January 2025 |work=Fenerbahce.org |language=tr}}</ref> On 8 March 2024, he made his continental debut with the team in a 3-0 away victory against [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union SG]], also made an assist.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/3/union-sg-0-3-fenerbahce |title=Union SG 0-3 Fenerbahçe |access-date=27 January 2025 |work=Fenerbahce.org |date=8 March 2024 |language=tr}}</ref>

He scored twice in his first half-season, including the only goal on 19 May away to rivals [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Agencies |first=Daily Sabah with |date=20 May 2024 |title=Galatasaray's title bid stalls as Fenerbahçe win in dramatic derby |url=https://www.dailysabah.com/sports/football/galatasarays-title-bid-stalls-as-fenerbahce-win-in-dramatic-derby |access-date=16 July 2024 |website=Daily Sabah}}</ref> His move became permanent on 1 July, on a three-year deal with the option for one more. Atlético, who had paid no fee to sign him, received €8 million in the deal.<ref name="marca" />

==International career==
In November 2015, he was called up to [[Turkey national football team]] by coach [[Fatih Terim]], following the injury of central defender [[Serdar Aziz]].<ref name="NationalTeamCallUp1">{{cite news |date=15 November 2015 |title=Hedefim kalıcı olmak |trans-title=My goal is to become permanent. |url=http://www.haberturk.com/spor/futbol/haber/1153662-hedefim-kalici-olmak |access-date=17 November 2015 |publisher=[[Habertürk]] |language=tr}}</ref><ref name="NationalTeamCallUp2">{{cite news |date=14 November 2015 |title=Terim'den sürpriz davet! |trans-title=A surprise call-up from Terim! |url=http://www.ntvspor.net/haber/futbol/142952/terimden-surpriz-davet |access-date=22 November 2015 |publisher=[[NTV Spor]] |language=tr}}</ref>

Söyüncü is the first Altınordu player called up to Turkey national football team after 78 years, since [[Sait Altınordu]], the iconic player of the club, was selected in 1937.<ref name="National Team Debut TFF">{{cite news |date=29 April 2016 |title=İzmir'in son gururu: Çağlar Söyüncü |trans-title=İzmir's latest pride: Çağlar Söyüncü |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=24983&1317pg=12 |access-date=8 October 2016 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |language=tr}}</ref> He is also the first player called up to national team from any İzmir-based football clubs since 1997. On 17 November 2015, Söyüncü was a reserve for the friendly game against [[Greece national football team|Greece]], but stayed on the bench and did not actually get a chance to play.<ref>{{Cite web |title=TÜRKİYE 0-0 YUNANİSTAN - A Milli Takım Haber Detayları TFF |trans-title=TURKEY 0-0 GREECE – National Team News Details TFF |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=24117 |access-date=2025-04-19 |website=www.tff.org}}</ref> On 18 March 2016, he was called to national squad for friendly games against [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] and [[Austria national football team|Austria]], to be held on 24 March 2016 in Antalya, Turkey and on 29 March in Austria, respectively.<ref name="Friendlies: Sweden and Austria, 2016 [1]">{{cite news |date=18 March 2016 |title=A Milli Takım'ın İsveç ve Avusturya maçları aday kadrosu ve programı |trans-title=The national team’s squad and schedule for the matches against Sweden and Austria. |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=24731 |access-date=19 March 2016 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |language=tr}}</ref><ref name="Friendlies: Sweden and Austria, 2016 [2]">{{cite news |date=18 March 2016 |title=A Milli Takımı'nın Aday Kadrosu Açıkandı |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/a-milli-futbol-takimi-nin-aday---2212072-skorerhaber/ |access-date=19 March 2016 |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |language=tr}}</ref> Substituting for [[Ozan Tufan]] in the dying minutes of a friendly game against Sweden, Söyüncü earned his first senior national team cap on 24 March 2016.<ref name="Friendlies: Sweden and Austria, 2016 [3]">{{cite news |title=Türkiye 2–1 İsveç |url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=24764 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=24 March 2016 |access-date=24 March 2016 |language=tr}}</ref> Earning his second cap, he was in the starting line-up in the friendly with [[Russia national football team|Russia]] on 1 September 2016, which ended 0–0.<ref name="Turkey - Russia friendly">{{cite news |title=Türkiye – Rusya: 0–0 |url=http://www.ntv.com.tr/spor/turkiye-rusya-0-0,qjgdRrXD3UmaJeICuXggKA |publisher=[[NTV Spor]] |date=1 September 2016 |access-date=8 October 2016 |language=tr}}</ref> On 1 June 2018, Söyüncü scored his first senior international goal on a friendly game against [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]], held at [[Stade de Genève]], [[Geneva]], Switzerland.<ref name="First Senior International Goal">{{cite news |date=1 May 2018 |title=Tunus - Türkiye Maç Detayı - TFF |trans-title=Tunisia - Turkey Match Details - TFF |url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=194085 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20191108132736/https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=29&macId=194085 |archive-date=8 November 2019 |access-date=8 November 2019 |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |language=Tr}}</ref> On 1 June 2021, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=35271 |title=A Millî Takımın nihai kadrosu açıklandı |trans-title=Final squad of the national team announced |work=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=1 June 2021 |access-date=1 June 2021 |language=tr}}</ref> On 24 May 2024, he was named in the 35-man preliminary squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=24 May 2024 |title=A Millî Takımımızın EURO 2024 Geniş Kadrosu Açıklandı |trans-title=EURO 2024 squad of our national team announced |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44364 |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |access-date=30 May 2024}}</ref> However, on 29 May, he was withdrawn due to injury.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=44426 |title=
Çağlar Söyüncü, A Millî Takım Aday Kadrosundan Çıkarıldı |trans-title=Çağlar Söyüncü was removed from the National Team Candidate Squad |language=tr |publisher=[[Turkish Football Federation]] |date=29 May 2024 |access-date=1 June 2024}}</ref>

==Style of play and reception==
Possessing leadership attributes, Söyüncü is good at playmaking, dribbling and timing.<ref name="Four Four Two Turkish Edition">{{cite web |date=16 November 2015 |title=Bu çocukta iş var: Çağlar Söyüncü (Altınordu) |url=http://fourfourtwo.com.tr/2015/11/16/bu-cocukta-is-var-caglar-soyuncu-altinordu/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624094150/http://fourfourtwo.com.tr/2015/11/16/bu-cocukta-is-var-caglar-soyuncu-altinordu/ |archive-date=24 June 2016 |access-date=22 March 2016 |publisher=[[Four Four Two|Four Four Two Turkish Edition]] |language=tr}}</ref> Standing at {{cvt|1.85|m||}}, he is strong in the air.<ref name="Four Four Two Turkish Edition"/> In 2016, he stated that his idol is Spanish defender [[Carles Puyol]] and he admires German international [[Mats Hummels]].<ref name="Admiration: Puyol and Hummels">{{cite news |date=8 May 2016 |title=A Milli Takımı'nın Aday Kadrosu Açıkandı |trans-title=The national team's preliminary squad has been announced. |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/caglar-soyuncu-bundesliga-nin---2241436-skorerhaber/ |access-date=8 October 2016 |publisher=[[Milliyet]] |language=tr}}</ref>

Former [[England national football team|English international]] and current [[Punditry|pundit]] [[Martin Keown]] analysed Söyüncü for ''[[BBC Sport]]'' in 2019, describing him "a defender made for the modern game", highlighting his agility, aggressiveness and heading attributes.<ref name="2019 Keown Analysis">{{cite news |last=Keown |first=Martin |author-link=Martin Keown |title=Leicester defender Caglar Soyuncu is 'a defender made for the modern game' - Martin Keown analysis |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50284368 |url-status=live |website=BBC Sport |date=3 November 2019 |access-date=7 November 2019 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20191107155946/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50284368 |archive-date=7 November 2019 |language=tr}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Söyüncü is a longtime fan of [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] since his childhood.<ref>{{cite news |title=Fenerbahçe formalı bu miniği tanıdınız mı? Çocukluk hayalini gerçekleştirdi |url=https://spor.haber7.com/foto-galeri/65288-fenerbahce-formali-bu-minigi-tanidiniz-mi-cocukluk-hayalini-gerceklestirdi/p7 |access-date=13 October 2020 |website=haber7.com |language=tr}}</ref>

